1 (b) Members of the task force who are not members of the Legislature
2 shall be nonvoting, ex officio members.
3 (4) The chairperson of the task force shall be the chairperson of
4 the Revenue Committee of the Legislature. Any staff support needed for
5 the task force shall be fulfilled by the staff of the Revenue Committee
6 of the Legislature.
7 (5) The members of the task force shall serve on the task force
8 without compensation.
9 (6) On or before December 1 of each year, the task force shall
10 submit a report containing the results of its work study and its
11 recommendations, if any, together with drafts of legislation necessary to
12 carry out its recommendations. The reports shall be submitted
13 electronically to the Clerk of the Legislature.
